==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hiatus
<hw>Hi*a"tus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> L.
<plw>Hiatus</plw>, E. <plw>Hiatuses</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.,
fr. <ets>hiare</ets>, <ets>hiatum</ets>, to gape; akin to E.
<ets>yawn</ets>. See <er>Yawn</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An opening;
an aperture; a gap; a chasm; esp., a defect in a manuscript, where some
part is lost or effaced; a space where something is wanting; a
break.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>The concurrence of two vowels in
two successive words or syllables.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hibbertia</ent>⟦br⟧
